    Training naïve Bayes

    To train your naïve Bayes classifier, you have to perform the following steps:

    1) Get or annotate a dataset with positive and negative tweets

    2) Preprocess the tweets: process_tweet(tweet) ➞ [w1, w2, w3, ...]:

    • Lowercase

    • Remove punctuation, urls, names

    • Remove stop words

    • Stemming

    • Tokenize sentences

    3) Compute freq(w, class):

    4) Get \(P(w | pos), P(w | neg) \)

    You can use the table above to compute the probabilities.

    5) Get λ(w)\lambda (w)λ(w)

    λ(w)=log⁡P(w∣pos)P(w∣neg) \lambda(w)=\log \frac{P(\mathrm{w} \mid \mathrm{pos})}{P(\mathrm{w} \mid \mathrm{neg})} λ(w)=logP(w∣neg)P(w∣pos)​

    6) Compute logprior=log⁡(P(pos)/P(neg))logprior = \log(P(pos) / P(neg))logprior=log(P(pos)/P(neg))

     logprior =log⁡DposDneg \text { logprior }=\log \frac{D_{p o s}}{D_{n e g}}  logprior =logDneg​Dpos​​, where DposD_{pos}Dpos​ and Dneg D_{neg} Dneg​ correspond to the number of positive and negative documents respectively.
